Anonymous Sat 04 May 2019 19:05:27 No.22919017 Report
Quoted By:
>>22918915

>trying to get better at writing.

Do yourself a favor and drink a beer, then record yourself telling a story about something that happened in your life. Watch it the next day and take notes about when you get bored of the video. Drink another beer and tell a different story, trying to apply the lessons you learned from the last one.

Alcohol is a social lubricant, and a single can of beer is enough to get your shit loosened up enough to talk about stuff in front of a camera without completely losing track of what you're supposed to be doing.

Entertaining writing is the spoken word being slapped on paper, minus the benefit of body language and pheromones. Video helps you remove the latter and teaches you about the stupid shit you do when you speak, so you can remove those garbage habits and grow more confident in social situations, allowing you to more freely speak and thus allowing you to do better writing.

t. retired writer
